[normal]              
[normal]We have gone for a completely different model
[normal],
[normal] which is incredibly fragmented. Most of the rest of the world come here and say, “How in the hell does this ever work with no co-ordination of a few dominant operators in the whole thing?” That is the model we start from. 
[normal]              
[normal]In many ways I would say we are an industry set up for conflict. Our charters are drawn up by some 
[normal]lawyers, and they are 
[normal]very smart lawyers
[normal],
[normal] but the principle was, “Via a series of penalties, claims and legal contracts
[normal],
[normal] we will force you to work together
[normal],
[normal] otherwise bad things will happen
[normal].”
